go_data.justification: CKD patients have elevated phosphate and FGF-23 concentrations, indicating FGF-23's role in phosphate metabolism.

go_data.term: negative regulation of vitamin D biosynthetic process
go_data.justification: FGF23 inhibits 1-alpha hydroxylase, reducing the renal synthesis of 1,25(OH)2D.
Osteocytes secrete FGF23, suggesting FGF-23's involvement in osteocyte function.
FGF23 binds to Klotho, implying it interacts at the cell surface.
